val operatingHours = spark.sql("""
SELECT
  business_id,
  state,
  city,
  neighborhood,
  array(split(hours.Monday, '-'), split(hours.Tuesday, '-'), split(hours.Wednesday, '-'), split(hours.Thursday, '-'), split(hours.Friday, '-')) as hours
FROM businesses
WHERE state IS NOT NULL
AND city IS NOT NULL
AND neighborhood IS NOT NULL
""")
operatingHours.createOrReplaceTempView("operating_hours")
operatingHours.printSchema

%sql
SELECT
  percentile(day_opening, 0.95)
FROM (
  SELECT
    split(day_operating_hours[0], ':')[0] * 60 + split(day_operating_hours[0], ':')[1] AS day_opening,
    split(day_operating_hours[1], ':')[0] * 60 + split(day_operating_hours[1], ':')[1] AS day_closing,
    day_operating_hours
  FROM (
    SELECT
      business_id,
      EXPLODE(hours) AS day_operating_hours
    FROM operating_hours
    ORDER BY 1
  )
  WHERE day_operating_hours IS NOT NULL
)
